  "diagnosis": "DUAL SHIFT (label + feature distributions): H(Y) drops 37% from train to test due to label distribution shift (test is 89% one class). Raw MI drops from 1.483 to 0.634 bits (ratio 0.43), but the Fano ceiling RISES to 99.3% because the near-pure test set is intrinsically easier. The CROSS-TEMPORAL MI = 0.421 bits (ceiling 96.7%) reveals the real degradation: train-era feature neighborhoods lose 34% of the within-test MI, confirming covariate shift. Per-feature: gas_price features collapse (-83%), while AI-detection features (behavioral_consistency, error_recovery_pattern) are temporally stable. This explains the Paper 1 temporal holdout AUC drop from 0.80 to 0.67.",
